        text-decoration: none;
        border-radius: 4px;
        transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
    }

        .contact-button:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
</style>

<h2>@ViewData["Title"]</h2>

<div class="highlight">
    <p>
        This Privacy Policy outlines how our clinic collects, uses, and protects the personal information of our patients and visitors. Please read this policy carefully to understand how we handle your data.
    </p>
</div>

<h3>Data Collection</h3>
<p>
    We collect the following information when you visit our clinic:
</p>

<ul class="highlight">
    <li>  Personal Information: This includes details such as the patient's name, date of birth, gender, address, contact number, and email address. These details help in identifying and communicating with the patient.</li>

    <li> Medical History: Clinics often ask for information about a patient's past and current medical conditions, previous surgeries, allergies, medications, and any ongoing treatments. This information helps healthcare providers understand the patient's health background and make informed decisions about their care.</li>

    <li> Insurance Information: Patients are usually asked to provide details of their health insurance coverage, including the insurance company's name, policy number, and group number. This information helps clinics in billing and processing insurance claims.</li>

    <li> Emergency Contacts: It is common for clinics to request the name, relationship, and contact information of a person to be contacted in case of an emergency.</li>

    <li>  Consent and Authorization: Clinics may ask patients to sign consent forms, authorizing the clinic to provide medical care, share medical records with other healthcare providers, and comply with privacy regulations.</li>

    <li> Payment Information: When patients receive medical services, clinics may need to collect payment information, such as credit card details or insurance billing information, to process payments.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Data Usage</h3>
<p>
    The information collected is used for the following purposes:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>To provide medical services and treatments</li>
    <li>To communicate with patients regarding their appointments and healthcare</li>
    <li>To improve the quality of our services</li>
</ul>

<h3>Data Protection</h3>
<p>
    We take the privacy and security of your personal information seriously. We have implemented measures to safeguard your data from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure.
</p>

<h3>Third-Party Disclosure</h3>
<p>
    We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to third parties without your consent, except as required by law or to provide necessary medical services.
</p>

<h3>Changes to the Privacy Policy</h3>
<p>
    We reserve the right to modify or update this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be reflected on this page, and we encourage you to review this policy periodically.
</p>

